1
00:00:12,839 --> 00:00:15,039
(Sanyin Sword)
(Knowing past lives denotes Fate Level.)

2
00:00:15,720 --> 00:00:17,879
(Predicting the future
denotes Vision Level.)

3
00:00:18,879 --> 00:00:21,039
(Eliminating hassle
denotes Clearance Level.)

4
00:00:21,440 --> 00:00:24,600
(Passing three levels leads to Sanda.)

5
00:00:26,519 --> 00:00:29,679
(Fang Junyu,
the previous dynasty's swordsman,)

6
00:00:29,960 --> 00:00:31,879
(created the Sanda Sword
based on Buddhism.)

7
00:00:33,280 --> 00:00:35,240
(His disciple, Master Shi Qugu,)

8
00:00:35,240 --> 00:00:36,759
(converted to the Southern Shaolin)

9
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:38,880
(and became the chief
of the Bodhi Department.)

10
00:00:39,399 --> 00:00:42,399
(He evolves the swordsmanship
with three signs)

11
00:00:42,920 --> 00:00:44,880
(into the Sanyin Sword.)

12
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:47,759
(The first move,)

13
00:00:48,359 --> 00:00:49,159
(Wuchang.)

14
00:00:49,840 --> 00:00:51,920
(The Wuchang Technique is concise.)

15
00:00:52,359 --> 00:00:53,640
(Its core lies)

16
00:00:54,159 --> 00:00:55,479
(in finding the enemy's flaws)

17
00:00:55,479 --> 00:00:56,640
(to conquer them.)

18
00:00:57,479 --> 00:01:00,200
(Always let the opponent strike first.)

19
00:01:01,520 --> 00:01:02,600
If a swordsman

20
00:01:02,600 --> 00:01:04,200
makes powerful and stunning moves,

21
00:01:04,599 --> 00:01:05,799
the point is not to draw the sword

22
00:01:06,280 --> 00:01:08,359
but to conceal it.

23
00:01:16,680 --> 00:01:18,000
Before the sword is unsheathed,

24
00:01:18,480 --> 00:01:20,439
no one knows where it will strike

25
00:01:20,680 --> 00:01:22,879
or the direction of the attack.

26
00:01:22,879 --> 00:01:24,040
Thus, there are no flaws.

27
00:01:24,439 --> 00:01:25,920
No one can escape.

28
00:01:27,840 --> 00:01:30,480
Find the flaw and strike swiftly.

29
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:31,680
And the outcome becomes clear.

30
00:01:33,480 --> 00:01:36,079
Next, the attack path
is a spiral straight line.

31
00:01:38,319 --> 00:01:40,480
How to achieve
the ultimate attack speed?

32
00:01:41,719 --> 00:01:43,480
The distance between the sword blade
and the flaw

33
00:01:43,719 --> 00:01:45,040
is the shortest straight line.

34
00:01:45,840 --> 00:01:46,920
Wuchang Technique's attack path

35
00:01:46,920 --> 00:01:49,519
must be a direct line.

36
00:01:50,599 --> 00:01:52,280
Between the two points,

37
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:54,560
the fastest is neither an arc
nor a straight line

38
00:01:55,799 --> 00:01:56,879
but a spiral straight line.

39
00:01:58,239 --> 00:02:00,519
So when the Wuchang Technique
is executed,

40
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:03,400
the wrist performs a rotation
close to a full circle,

41
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:07,120
moving in a spiral straight line

42
00:02:09,240 --> 00:02:12,360
to maximize speed and destructive power.

43
00:02:15,599 --> 00:02:17,240
The second move, Wuwo.

44
00:02:17,520 --> 00:02:20,360
Martial arts philosophy originates
from the principle of Wuwo.

45
00:02:20,680 --> 00:02:22,360
Respond with a single technique.

46
00:02:22,560 --> 00:02:24,639
Meet myriad changes with constancy.

47
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:28,159
The Wuwo Technique
is the strongest defensive move.

48
00:02:28,639 --> 00:02:29,560
Since it is defensive,

49
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:31,840
it demands the largest defensive area.

50
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:32,800
For a sword,

51
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:34,599
it can be seen as a line.

52
00:02:35,560 --> 00:02:36,479
Dots move to form a line.

53
00:02:36,479 --> 00:02:37,560
Lines move to form a surface.

54
00:02:37,960 --> 00:02:38,680
And a circle

55
00:02:38,680 --> 00:02:41,159
is the largest shape it can be.

56
00:02:42,960 --> 00:02:45,919
Constant rotation
increases its gravity acceleration.

57
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:47,800
While defending,

58
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:50,240
we turn the opponent's attack
into a reactive force.

59
00:02:56,919 --> 00:02:57,599
(The third move,)

60
00:02:58,080 --> 00:02:59,080
(Nirvana.)

61
00:02:59,879 --> 00:03:02,840
(The martial arts philosophy originates
from the tranquility of nirvana.)

62
00:03:03,479 --> 00:03:05,360
(The core strategy lies
in rapid change.)

63
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:07,639
(In the moment of action,)

64
00:03:07,639 --> 00:03:09,439
(the sword's path
takes various changes.)

65
00:03:09,719 --> 00:03:12,000
(Each change conceals a deadly threat,)

66
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:14,719
(leaving the opponent no opportunity
to respond.)

67
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:31,680
(The merit of the Wuchang Technique)

68
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:33,439
(lies in its concept-oriented approach.)

69
00:03:34,120 --> 00:03:36,879
(Operating the swordsmanship
through subtle tactics.)

70
00:03:37,479 --> 00:03:39,479
(A learner with basics can do it.)

71
00:03:40,199 --> 00:03:42,919
(There's no need to practice
for years or even decades.)

72
00:03:43,560 --> 00:03:46,240
(There are no requirements
for physical fitness or inner strength.)

73
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:50,199
(However, Wuwo and Nirvana Technique
cannot be quickly mastered.)

74
00:03:50,439 --> 00:03:53,800
(One must practice daily
to make incremental progress.)

