00:14:00,159 --> 00:14:00,960
Stir-fried pork.

277
00:14:01,320 --> 00:14:02,759
We must try the roast duck.

278
00:14:02,759 --> 00:14:03,960
Ding Yu.

279
00:14:03,960 --> 00:14:05,080
There are just three of us.

280
00:14:05,080 --> 00:14:06,159
Too much food.

281
00:14:06,440 --> 00:14:07,159
It's alright.

282
00:14:07,159 --> 00:14:10,080
Pea flour pastry,
fried stuffed bun, Rolling Donkey,

283
00:14:10,559 --> 00:14:12,000
and Douzhi.

284
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:12,720
How about it?

285
00:14:13,240 --> 00:14:13,919
Waiter!

286
00:14:14,399 --> 00:14:15,360
We're ordering dishes.

287
00:14:15,600 --> 00:14:16,159
Coming.

288
00:14:18,112 --> 00:14:18,679
Sirs.

289
00:14:18,679 --> 00:14:19,440
Listen.

290
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:20,919
Sixi meatballs,

291
00:14:21,080 --> 00:14:21,759
crispy pork.

292
00:14:21,759 --> 00:14:22,304
Wait a moment.

293
00:14:23,960 --> 00:14:26,440
I saw an old acquaintance.

294
00:14:30,624 --> 00:14:31,296
(Baoxinglong)

295
00:14:32,320 --> 00:14:32,960
Senior.

296
00:14:35,960 --> 00:14:36,559
Senior.

297
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:39,039
Greetings.

298
00:14:39,720 --> 00:14:41,039
Who is your senior?

299
00:14:41,639 --> 00:14:43,279
You have saved my life twice.

300
00:14:43,759 --> 00:14:45,039
I am grateful to you.

301
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:46,960
That's because you shouldn't die.

302
00:14:46,960 --> 00:14:48,279
I just came across you.

303
00:14:50,519 --> 00:14:51,720
I didn't mean to save you.

304
00:14:52,679 --> 00:14:55,039
Whether it was an unintentional act

305
00:14:55,039 --> 00:14:56,039
or not,

306
00:14:56,440 --> 00:14:58,440
you saved me, anyway.

307
00:15:00,120 --> 00:15:02,919
You've come from Shanxi
to the capital so quickly.

308
00:15:03,799 --> 00:15:06,000
Have you caught the person
you are after?

309
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:06,600
Not yet.

310
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:09,879
The people I'm after
have also come to the capital.

311
00:15:10,399 --> 00:15:11,840
But I still haven't found them.

312
00:15:14,480 --> 00:15:15,480
I ask for your advice.

313
00:15:15,759 --> 00:15:16,840
On what?

314
00:15:16,840 --> 00:15:18,840
You helped me twice.

315
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:20,480
Otherwise,
I couldn't have had any clues.

316
00:15:20,840 --> 00:15:23,360
Although I don't know who you are

317
00:15:23,600 --> 00:15:24,360
or what you're up to.

318
00:15:24,960 --> 00:15:27,080
I can't deny
that you've been helping me.

319
00:15:27,240 --> 00:15:29,399
When I don't know what to do now,

320
00:15:29,399 --> 00:15:30,240
you appear.

321
00:15:31,159 --> 00:15:32,799
Aren't you here to give me advice?

322
00:15:33,799 --> 00:15:36,039
You can't be just a local constable.

323
00:15:37,679 --> 00:15:38,639
You should go home.

324
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:40,679
Yes.

325
00:15:40,679 --> 00:15:42,200
Once the case is closed, I will go home.

326
00:15:43,720 --> 00:15:45,519
Didn't you ask me to enlighten you?

327
00:15:45,639 --> 00:15:46,960
I'm telling you to go home.

328
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:52,159
You're too slow.

329
00:15:52,159 --> 00:15:54,279
Must I spell it out for you?

330
00:15:54,759 --> 00:15:55,919
Go back to Dagu.

331
00:15:56,519 --> 00:15:58,480
The person you're chasing is there.

332
00:15:59,879 --> 00:16:01,279
Zhuo Bufan has gone to Dagu?

333
00:16:01,279 --> 00:16:03,480
The case started from Dagu,
and he has returned there.

334
00:16:04,039 --> 00:16:04,840
This is...

335
00:16:04,840 --> 00:16:05,720
Don't ask me.

336
00:16:06,039 --> 00:16:07,279
Figure it out yourself.

337
00:16:07,279 --> 00:16:07,879
Senior.

338
00:16:09,759 --> 00:16:11,159
You must know a lot.

339
00:16:11,679 --> 00:16:13,080
Can you tell me more?

340
00:16:19,080 --> 00:16:20,840
The future is unpredictable.

341
00:16:21,559 --> 00:16:23,519
Hard times make people gloomy.

342
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:26,759
You bear a mission
and a heavy responsibility.

343
00:16:27,440 --> 00:16:28,120
Wang Jialuo.

344
00:16:29,240 --> 00:16:30,279
You must survive.

345
00:16:32,320 --> 00:16:32,864
Senior.

346
00:16:47,799 --> 00:16:49,960
The Douzhi tastes terrible.

347
00:16:58,399 --> 00:17:00,919
I've arranged everything.

348
00:17:01,039 --> 00:17:02,799
Your assignment to the south

349
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:03,919
has also been issued.

350
00:17:04,759 --> 00:17:06,480
Set off as soon as possible.

351
00:17:07,079 --> 00:17:07,640
Yes.

352
00:17:08,759 --> 00:17:10,480
Do you understand

353
00:17:10,839 --> 00:17:11,720
the arrangement?

354
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:13,480
I understand.

355
00:17:14,079 --> 00:17:15,480
You ask me to leave

356
00:17:15,480 --> 00:17:16,240
to wait...

357
00:17:18,680 --> 00:17:20,119
When the rebellion starts,

358
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:21,319
I can avoid suspicion.

359
00:17:21,759 --> 00:17:22,559
That's right.

360
00:17:23,680 --> 00:17:25,839
At the same time,
you can command the troops

361
00:17:25,839 --> 00:17:28,519
in the south to back me up.

362
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:31,079
If bad things happen,

363
00:17:31,359 --> 00:17:32,480
I'll have a way out.

364
00:17:32,799 --> 00:17:33,920
Everything will

365
00:17:33,960 --> 00:17:34,920
go smoothly.

366
00:17:36,720 --> 00:17:38,400
I've always felt

367
00:17:38,759 --> 00:17:41,359
the Altar Treasure
will eventually reappear

368
00:17:41,880 --> 00:17:44,200
in Fujian.

369
00:17:44,440 --> 00:17:49,640
So when thinking whether you should go
to Jiangsu and Zhejiang,

370
00:17:50,279 --> 00:17:51,680
or Fujian,

371
00:17:52,519 --> 00:17:53,920
after careful consideration,

372
00:17:54,640 --> 00:17:55,480
I decided

373
00:17:56,240 --> 00:17:57,319
to let you go to Fujian.

374
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:01,279
Father.

375
00:18:01,279 --> 00:18:03,319
And the people you sent
to track down the Altar Treasure?

376
00:18:03,319 --> 00:18:06,319
Zhuo Bufan failed at Futu Temple.

377
00:18:06,440 --> 00:18:07,799
The clues there fell

378
00:18:08,160 --> 00:18:10,039
into the hands
of the Imperial Household Department.

379
00:18:11,519 --> 00:18:12,480
Don't worry.

380
00:18:14,160 --> 00:18:16,640
The item is
with the Imperial Household Department.

381
00:18:16,640 --> 00:18:18,559
It's not hard to get it.

382
00:18:20,720 --> 00:18:23,200
However, unexpectedly,

383
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:26,279
Zhuo Bufan sent me a message.

384
00:18:27,720 --> 00:18:28,920
I originally thought

385
00:18:28,920 --> 00:18:30,640
that finding the other half
of the treasure map

386
00:18:30,640 --> 00:18:32,279
would reveal the truth.

387
00:18:32,279 --> 00:18:33,519
But now I know

388
00:18:34,119 --> 00:18:36,359
there are three parts
to the treasure map.

389
00:18:36,519 --> 00:18:37,799
Did Zhuo Bufan find out

390
00:18:37,799 --> 00:18:39,039
the whereabouts of the third map?

391
00:18:39,720 --> 00:18:41,200
There's a slight possibility

392
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:43,160
that it's in the Tianjin Presidio.

393
00:18:43,880 --> 00:18:45,039
Zhuo Bufan went to investigate it.

394
00:18:46,279 --> 00:18:48,920
Tianjin happens to
be where my troops are stationed.

395
00:18:48,920 --> 00:18:50,680
Should I arrange for someone
to check it out?

396
00:18:51,839 --> 00:18:52,359
No.

397
00:18:53,720 --> 00:18:55,799
Just pretend you know nothing.

398
00:18:57,319 --> 00:19:00,400
Beiyang is already taking action

399
00:19:00,400 --> 00:19:01,599
on the treasure.

400
00:19:01,839 --> 00:19:03,319
If you act,

401
00:19:03,319 --> 00:19:06,440
it will attract a lot of attention.

402
00:19:06,799 --> 00:19:09,160
And it might even

403
00:19:09,160 --> 00:19:10,839
alert the opposition.

404
00:19:12,160 --> 00:19:13,920
I used outsiders

405
00:19:14,480 --> 00:19:17,720
just to avoid arousing suspicion.

406
00:19:17,960 --> 00:19:20,200
Is Zhuo Bufan reliable?

407
00:19:25,240 --> 00:19:28,480
There are no reliable people

408
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:31,599
but reliable leverages.

409
00:19:33,119 --> 00:19:34,839
Your father-in-law
sent Zhuo Bufan to Tianjin?

410
00:19:35,319 --> 00:19:35,960
Yes.

411
00:19:39,440 --> 00:19:40,200
I see.

412
00:19:41,079 --> 00:19:42,279
You don't need to worry about it.

413
00:19:42,640 --> 00:19:43,440
Someone is on it.

414
00:19:44,559 --> 00:19:45,480
Mr. Xie.

415
00:19:45,480 --> 00:19:46,720
Do I need to send someone...?

416
00:19:46,720 --> 00:19:47,264
No need.

417
00:19:48,440 --> 00:19:49,960
Someone is
in charge of the secret treasure.

418
00:19:50,400 --> 00:19:51,920
You don't have to intervene.

419
00:20:01,039 --> 00:20:02,119
Do you know

420
00:20:02,799 --> 00:20:04,759
why your father-in-law wanted you
to go to Fujian

421
00:20:05,640 --> 00:20:06,759
and we agreed to let you go?

422
00:20:09,039 --> 00:20:09,568
I don't know.

423
00:20:10,839 --> 00:20:12,880
If I don't trust you,

424
00:20:13,440 --> 00:20:15,160
can you be transferred to Fujian

425
00:20:15,759 --> 00:20:16,480
so quickly?

426
00:20:17,839 --> 00:20:20,519
Beiyang fully trusts you.

427
00:20:21,319 --> 00:20:23,079
Your transfer to Fujian

428
00:20:23,200 --> 00:20:25,319
seems like your father-in-law's move.

429
00:20:26,559 --> 00:20:29,680
But actually, it's our biggest chip.

430
00:20:29,759 --> 00:20:31,680
Don't ruin the whole plan

431
00:20:32,200 --> 00:20:33,359
for some trivial matters.

432
00:20:34,160 --> 00:20:34,839
Understood.

433
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:36,319
Thanks for your advice.

434
00:20:39,640 --> 00:20:41,240
Men Sandao kept Liu Lin

435
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:42,839
by his side

436
00:20:42,839 --> 00:20:44,599
instead of sending her
to the Ministry of Justice.

437
00:20:44,599 --> 00:20:46,039
It means this woman

438
00:20:46,039 --> 00:20:48,279
surely holds some important secrets.

439
00:20:48,599 --> 00:20:51,559
Men Sandao cannot always
keep her by his side.

440
00:20:52,519 --> 00:20:56,039
He can't take her
with him to the palace.

441
00:20:56,599 --> 00:20:58,440
Are you thinking of abducting her?

442
00:20:58,960 --> 00:21:00,000
This woman

443
00:21:00,519 --> 00:21:02,920
probably will not cooperate
with Men Sandao.

444
00:21:04,519 --> 00:21:05,680
It makes sense.

445
00:21:06,240 --> 00:21:07,839
Men Sandao has to

446
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:09,920
keep her with him.

447
00:21:10,279 --> 00:21:12,839
He can't get the information
he wants to know.

448
00:21:13,319 --> 00:21:16,319
We can try the hallucinogen.

449
00:21:16,599 --> 00:21:18,119
Now that things have come to this,

450
00:21:18,119 --> 00:21:19,079
perhaps

451
00:21:20,039 --> 00:21:21,720
we can use it to get answers.

452
00:21:22,160 --> 00:21:22,839
Yes.

453
00:21:23,839 --> 00:21:27,519
Then I'll arrange it.

454
00:21:30,759 --> 00:21:32,319
Be careful not to clash

455
00:21:32,319 --> 00:21:34,240
with Men Sandao.

456
00:21:34,480 --> 00:21:36,640
Be careful.

457
00:21:56,160 --> 00:21:57,000
Help!

458
00:22:07,160 --> 00:22:09,319
They don't seem like your people.

459
00:22:13,920 --> 00:22:14,519
Perfect timing.

460
00:22:14,759 --> 00:22:15,759
Let me try the blade.

461
00:22:30,920 --> 00:22:32,960
(The first move, Wuchang.)

462
00:22:33,359 --> 00:22:35,200
(The Wuchang Technique is concise.)

463
00:22:35,640 --> 00:22:38,279
(The martial arts philosophy originates
from impermanent things.)

464
00:22:38,480 --> 00:22:40,440
(Always let the opponent strike first.)

465
00:22:41,119 --> 00:22:42,559
(Before the sword is unsheathed,)

466
00:22:42,920 --> 00:22:44,880
(no one knows where it will strike)

467
00:22:45,079 --> 00:22:47,240
(or the direction of the attack.)

468
00:22:47,240 --> 00:22:48,480
(Thus, there are no flaws.)

469
00:22:48,799 --> 00:22:50,640
(No one can escape.)

470
00:22:52,880 --> 00:22:55,200
(How to achieve
the ultimate attack speed?)

471
00:22:56,119 --> 00:22:58,000
(Between the two points,)

472
00:22:58,119 --> 00:22:59,720
(the fastest is neither an arc)

473
00:23:00,160 --> 00:23:01,160
(nor a straight line)

474
00:23:01,720 --> 00:23:04,000
(but a spiral straight line.)

475
00:23:18,079 --> 00:23:19,720
(The second move, Wuwo.)

476
00:23:20,799 --> 00:23:23,799
(The Wuwo Technique
is the strongest defensive move.)

477
00:23:24,200 --> 00:23:27,319
(Since it is defensive,
it demands the largest defensive area.)

478
00:23:27,319 --> 00:23:28,440
(For a sword,)

479
00:23:28,759 --> 00:23:30,240
(it can be seen as a line.)

480
00:23:31,119 --> 00:23:33,240
(Dots move to form a line.
Lines move to form a surface.)

481
00:23:33,240 --> 00:23:34,319
(Turn the square into a circle,)

482
00:23:34,319 --> 00:23:36,680
(thus forming a powerful shield.)

483
00:24:02,920 --> 00:24:03,559
Retreat.

484
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:20,039
You just utilized Sanyin Sword.

485
00:24:20,759 --> 00:24:21,799
But I used a blade.

486
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:24,079
No wonder it's not powerful.

487
00:24:24,559 --> 00:24:25,640
Isn't this powerful enough?

488
00:24:25,640 --> 00:24:26,880
If so, why did you get hurt?

489
00:24:38,160 --> 00:24:38,680
Bear with it.

490
00:24:43,680 --> 00:24:44,759
Who are they?

491
00:24:44,759 --> 00:24:46,480
Many people want to capture you,

492
00:24:46,480 --> 00:24:47,559
like Rongtian Ridge,

493
00:24:47,559 --> 00:24:48,559
the Japanese,

494
00:24:49,119 --> 00:24:50,720
and maybe Beiyang.

495
00:24:51,960 --> 00:24:53,160
They're not Beiyang Army.

496
00:24:53,799 --> 00:24:55,599
Beiyang has guns.

497
00:24:55,599 --> 00:24:56,519
You can't defeat guns.

498
00:24:56,640 --> 00:24:57,559
Who knows?

499
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:01,440
It's not Rongtian Ridge either.

500
00:25:01,440 --> 00:25:02,480
They don't have that many men.

501
00:25:02,480 --> 00:25:03,279
Moreover,

502
00:25:04,160 --> 00:25:05,920
you cannot beat Zhuo Bufan.

503
00:25:05,920 --> 00:25:07,519
It's still uncertain.

504
00:25:10,359 --> 00:25:12,559
Only the Japanese could use this.

505
00:25:13,599 --> 00:25:15,039
You were quite good at hitting them.

506
00:25:15,039 --> 00:25:16,279
They don't have any experts, right?

507
00:25:16,519 --> 00:25:17,279
What are you saying?

508
00:25:17,279 --> 00:25:17,880
Don't move.

509
00:25:20,519 --> 00:25:21,880
They're also looking for the treasure?

510
00:25:22,160 --> 00:25:23,720
Isn't that obvious...

511
00:25:23,720 --> 00:25:25,160
Don't move. Bear the pain.

512
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:29,759
If I'm captured by the Japanese,

513
00:25:29,880 --> 00:25:31,720
it's no different
from being imprisoned by you.

514
00:25:31,720 --> 00:25:32,680
There's a huge difference.

515
00:25:33,799 --> 00:25:35,160
If I find the secret treasure,

516
00:25:35,160 --> 00:25:36,799
the court can restore and recover.

517
00:25:37,119 --> 00:25:38,680
If Beiyang finds the secret treasure,

518
00:25:38,680 --> 00:25:40,200
they will become even more arrogant.

519
00:25:40,559 --> 00:25:42,200
But no matter who
finds the secret treasure,

520
00:25:42,200 --> 00:25:43,519
it's no good for the Japanese.

521
00:25:43,839 --> 00:25:45,359
So for them,

522
00:25:45,359 --> 00:25:46,559
it's best if no one finds it.

523
00:25:47,519 --> 00:25:48,839
If I were Japanese,

524
00:25:49,400 --> 00:25:51,359
capturing you would be

525
00:25:52,279 --> 00:25:53,440
more prudent than killing you.

526
00:25:53,720 --> 00:25:55,200
Then why didn't they just kill me?

527
00:25:56,599 --> 00:25:57,720
Everyone has greed.

528
00:25:57,960 --> 00:25:59,200
Perhaps they wanted

529
00:25:59,200 --> 00:26:01,400
to pry some secrets from you.

530
00:26:05,759 --> 00:26:06,640
Have you studied medicine?

531
00:26:06,640 --> 00:26:07,240
No.

532
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:09,880
I have treated the injuries

533
00:26:09,880 --> 00:26:10,799
of my comrades.

534
00:26:11,960 --> 00:26:12,720
Those injuries

535
00:26:13,319 --> 00:26:14,400
were mostly caused

536
00:26:14,400 --> 00:26:15,480
by the court's lapdogs like you.

537
00:26:21,519 --> 00:26:22,640
Could you call us Hounds?

538
00:26:22,640 --> 00:26:23,480
Don't call me a lapdog.

539
00:26:23,480 --> 00:26:25,119
That's too harsh.

540
00:26:27,759 --> 00:26:30,400
You Reformists have great courage

541
00:26:30,640 --> 00:26:32,160
but overestimate yourselves.

542
00:26:32,400 --> 00:26:34,359
A hundred or even dozens of people

543
00:26:34,359 --> 00:26:35,559
dare to start a rebellion?

544
00:26:35,559 --> 00:26:36,799
The dynasty is over 100 years old.

545
00:26:36,799 --> 00:26:38,480
With internal strife
and external threats,

546
00:26:38,480 --> 00:26:39,519
the country's power is waning.

547
00:26:39,519 --> 00:26:41,359
But it can't be overturned by Sun Wen,

548
00:26:41,359 --> 00:26:42,200
a guy who fled overseas.

549
00:26:42,200 --> 00:26:43,960
Nor reckless Reformists

550
00:26:43,960 --> 00:26:45,079
can shake it.

551
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:50,400
It's just a minor wound.

552
00:26:51,079 --> 00:26:51,880
It's not serious.

553
00:26:52,960 --> 00:26:54,279
But if left unattended,

554
00:26:54,960 --> 00:26:56,319
it will get infected and rot

555
00:26:56,599 --> 00:26:57,440
in a few days.

556
00:26:57,960 --> 00:26:59,240
If you keep ignoring it,

557
00:27:00,559 --> 00:27:02,359
the arm will soon become useless

558
00:27:02,359 --> 00:27:03,039
and be amputated.

559
00:27:04,319 --> 00:27:05,440
If you don't treat it,

560
00:27:05,839 --> 00:27:07,559
you will die as a result.

561
00:27:09,079 --> 00:27:10,319
Mr. Sun and the revolutionaries

562
00:27:10,319 --> 00:27:11,559
initiated revolts time and again.

563
00:27:12,160 --> 00:27:13,319
Seemingly it only

564
00:27:13,319 --> 00:27:14,359
causes a small wound.

565
00:27:15,839 --> 00:27:16,880
But the court no longer knows

566
00:27:16,880 --> 00:27:18,000
how to treat it.

567
00:27:19,480 --> 00:27:20,440
One day,

568
00:27:21,240 --> 00:27:22,559
this wound will spread.

569
00:27:23,039 --> 00:27:23,960
It will grow larger

570
00:27:24,680 --> 00:27:25,640
and ultimately be fatal.

571
00:27:26,079 --> 00:27:27,519
It's like the difference
between you and me.

572
00:27:27,640 --> 00:27:28,400
Mr. Muqing.

573
00:27:29,440 --> 00:27:30,279
You are very powerful.

574
00:27:30,720 --> 00:27:32,359
Your strength makes many people fear.

575
00:27:32,920 --> 00:27:34,240
But I have never been afraid of you.

576
00:27:34,559 --> 00:27:35,799
That is the power of revolution.

577
00:27:37,880 --> 00:27:38,799
I know

578
00:27:38,920 --> 00:27:40,240
I cannot shake you at this moment,

579
00:27:40,960 --> 00:27:42,319
but I will never give up.

580
00:27:42,880 --> 00:27:44,920
Even at the cost of my life, I will try.

581
00:27:46,000 --> 00:27:47,000
I firmly believe

582
00:27:47,400 --> 00:27:48,920
that I will ultimately win.

583
00:27:52,240 --> 00:27:53,559
What is the purpose of doing this?

584
00:27:53,880 --> 00:27:55,839
Can you watch and do nothing

585
00:27:55,839 --> 00:27:57,920
when the nation
and its people are in trouble?

586
00:27:59,319 --> 00:28:00,960
Why did the reform occur
during Guangxu's regime?

587
00:28:00,960 --> 00:28:01,920
Who will benefit?

588
00:28:01,920 --> 00:28:03,119
Who will suffer losses from it?

589
00:28:05,640 --> 00:28:06,839
Kang Youwei and Liang Qichao

590
00:28:07,480 --> 00:28:09,039
used to talk about these questions

591
00:28:09,039 --> 00:28:10,440
with the late Emperor.

592
00:28:10,960 --> 00:28:12,480
The reform benefits the country

593
00:28:12,799 --> 00:28:13,440
and the people

594
00:28:14,480 --> 00:28:16,279
at the cost
of the imperial family's interests.

595
00:28:18,680 --> 00:28:20,000
For this reason,

596
00:28:21,160 --> 00:28:22,680
the reform only lasted 100 days.

597
00:28:24,839 --> 00:28:25,680
I am Manchu.

598
00:28:26,640 --> 00:28:27,960
Though I am Manchu,

599
00:28:28,400 --> 00:28:29,119
I know

600
00:28:30,240 --> 00:28:31,440
if the court still regards the state

601
00:28:31,440 --> 00:28:32,839
as private property

602
00:28:32,839 --> 00:28:34,440
and maintains the imperial system

603
00:28:34,759 --> 00:28:36,279
instead of choosing constitutionalism,

604
00:28:36,960 --> 00:28:38,799
the nation will ultimately fall.

605
00:28:39,799 --> 00:28:40,680
Mr. Muqing.

606
00:28:41,079 --> 00:28:42,160
I've said it many times

607
00:28:42,160 --> 00:28:43,480
that you are not an ordinary hound.

608
00:28:43,880 --> 00:28:45,759
In fact, you've admitted the need
for change.

609
00:28:46,480 --> 00:28:47,400
You know it.

610
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:49,960
The current court is struggling.

611
00:28:50,079 --> 00:28:51,559
Yet at this time, they still refuse to

612
00:28:51,559 --> 00:28:52,680
give up the slightest benefits,

613
00:28:52,680 --> 00:28:54,640
leading the nation
into a desperate situation.

614
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:56,319
This country is full of hope.

615
00:28:56,680 --> 00:28:58,559
But the court is hopeless.

616
00:28:59,440 --> 00:29:01,640
You must believe in Mr. Sun
and Tongmenghui.

617
00:29:01,640 --> 00:29:02,279
I don't.

618
00:29:05,759 --> 00:29:07,240
Sun Wen has neither troops nor guns.

619
00:29:07,519 --> 00:29:09,000
He only has passionate

620
00:29:09,000 --> 00:29:10,440
but mindless lunatics like you.

621
00:29:10,519 --> 00:29:12,160
I do not believe that Tongmenghui

622
00:29:12,160 --> 00:29:13,440
has the ability to change the nation.

623
00:29:13,839 --> 00:29:15,240
I accept what you think.

624
00:29:15,240 --> 00:29:16,640
But I do not accept what you do.

625
00:29:16,640 --> 00:29:18,480
Striking a stone
with an egg yields no result.

626
00:29:19,119 --> 00:29:21,319
You have instigated dozens of uprisings,
both large and small.

627
00:29:21,319 --> 00:29:22,559
Each of them is a total failure

628
00:29:22,559 --> 00:29:24,119
and a total annihilation.

629
00:29:24,640 --> 00:29:26,039
After all this time,

630
00:29:26,039 --> 00:29:26,920
what has changed?

631
00:29:26,920 --> 00:29:27,640
Enlighten the people.

632
00:29:28,640 --> 00:29:30,079
Every act of rebellion and struggle

633
00:29:30,079 --> 00:29:31,359
enlightened the people.

634
00:29:31,359 --> 00:29:32,160
Save it.

635
00:29:32,839 --> 00:29:34,160
You really can't make it.

636
00:29:35,279 --> 00:29:35,880
It's okay.

637
00:29:36,680 --> 00:29:37,920
One day you will believe us.

638
00:29:39,039 --> 00:29:40,440
Do you know that Prince Regent Zaifeng

639
00:29:40,440 --> 00:29:42,039
is also actively
promoting constitutionalism?

640
00:29:42,559 --> 00:29:43,519
And he has already twice

641
00:29:43,519 --> 00:29:45,279
changed the scheduled date
for constitutionalism.

642
00:29:45,279 --> 00:29:47,960
It's moved up from 1917 to 1913.

643
00:29:48,440 --> 00:29:50,240
The court is not full of conservatives

644
00:29:50,240 --> 00:29:52,440
trying to preserve their interests
like you think.

645
00:29:52,440 --> 00:29:54,680
Some actively resort to the reform.

646
00:29:55,119 --> 00:29:57,039
I'm bound to support constitutionalism.

647
00:29:57,039 --> 00:29:58,519
But I will never allow you people

648
00:29:58,519 --> 00:30:00,839
to attempt to overthrow the court.

649
00:30:01,599 --> 00:30:03,119
I bear no malice towards you

650
00:30:03,119 --> 00:30:05,319
because I know
you are not doing this for yourselves.

651
00:30:05,319 --> 00:30:06,960
You do it all for the country
and the people.

652
00:30:08,079 --> 00:30:09,480
But you are oversimplifying things

653
00:30:09,480 --> 00:30:10,799
and acting too extremely.

654
00:30:11,480 --> 00:30:13,079
If you want to serve the country
and the people,

655
00:30:13,200 --> 00:30:14,440
just behave yourself.

656
00:30:14,440 --> 00:30:15,640
Don't cause trouble for the court.

657
00:30:16,279 --> 00:30:16,880
Prince Zaifeng...

658
00:30:19,640 --> 00:30:22,319
Prince Zaifeng will
eradicate the internal strife

659
00:30:22,319 --> 00:30:23,519
and promote constitutionalism.

660
00:30:28,920 --> 00:30:30,839
Given that you dressed my wound,

661
00:30:31,559 --> 00:30:33,880
I just gave you a chance
to talk about revolution.

662
00:30:33,880 --> 00:30:35,240
If you say it again, see you

663
00:30:35,440 --> 00:30:36,400
in the torture chamber.

664
00:30:36,839 --> 00:30:37,359
Wait.

665
00:30:37,960 --> 00:30:38,920
I didn't start it.

666
00:30:38,920 --> 00:30:39,839
It was you.

667
00:30:41,960 --> 00:30:43,319
You asked me if I had studied medicine.

668
00:30:43,440 --> 00:30:44,720
I said I had helped my comrades

669
00:30:44,720 --> 00:30:45,720
deal with injuries.

670
00:30:46,039 --> 00:30:47,279
Then you just started nagging,

671
00:30:47,279 --> 00:30:47,880
speaking ill

672
00:30:47,880 --> 00:30:49,680
of Tongmenghui.

673
00:30:49,680 --> 00:30:51,039
Considering your injury,

674
00:30:51,039 --> 00:30:52,200
I just talked a little with you.

675
00:30:52,200 --> 00:30:53,400
Now, you are finished

676
00:30:53,400 --> 00:30:54,720
and then start to blame me?

677
00:30:55,079 --> 00:30:55,960
Why are you angry?

678
00:30:55,960 --> 00:30:57,440
I didn't say I was going to torture you.

679
00:30:57,440 --> 00:30:58,559
You said you spare me this one.

680
00:30:58,559 --> 00:30:59,319
Why?

681
00:30:59,319 --> 00:31:00,279
You started it.

682
00:31:00,279 --> 00:31:01,480
Why am I to blame?

683
00:31:02,759 --> 00:31:03,720
Alright.

684
00:31:03,720 --> 00:31:04,519
Pretend I never said it.

685
00:31:05,400 --> 00:31:07,400
How could I?

686
00:31:07,400 --> 00:31:08,680
You have already said it.

687
00:31:08,680 --> 00:31:10,200
Can you take back your words?

688
00:31:10,200 --> 00:31:11,119
So what do you want?

689
00:31:11,400 --> 00:31:13,640
I'll save the chance for next time.

690
00:31:14,440 --> 00:31:17,079
Look how petty you are.

691
00:31:17,079 --> 00:31:18,519
You're all so small-minded.

692
00:31:18,519 --> 00:31:19,599
Can you guys change the nation?

693
00:31:20,240 --> 00:31:20,839
Make way.

694
00:31:29,519 --> 00:31:31,240
A dozen or so men went with you, right?

695
00:31:33,079 --> 00:31:34,039
15 people.

696
00:31:34,680 --> 00:31:36,799
15 people couldn't beat one person?

697
00:31:39,240 --> 00:31:43,039
Are the imperial guards so formidable?

698
00:31:43,559 --> 00:31:45,640
I didn't expect Men Sandao's kung fu

699
00:31:45,640 --> 00:31:46,759
to be so powerful.

700
00:31:47,440 --> 00:31:48,400
Had I known this,

701
00:31:48,400 --> 00:31:50,720
we should have killed Liu Lin.

702
00:31:54,240 --> 00:31:54,880
Forget it.

703
00:31:55,599 --> 00:31:57,319
You did your best. It's not your fault.

704
00:31:57,559 --> 00:31:59,200
Men Sandao

705
00:31:59,200 --> 00:32:00,960
is stronger than we thought.

706
00:32:01,880 --> 00:32:03,200
Anyway, he can't keep Liu Lin

707
00:32:03,200 --> 00:32:04,839
by his side every day.

708
00:32:05,559 --> 00:32:07,119
We can find another opportunity.

709
00:32:09,839 --> 00:32:12,559
Given Men Sandao's wisdom and ability,

710
00:32:12,839 --> 00:32:14,359
we failed this time.

711
00:32:14,920 --> 00:32:16,599
If we want to find another opportunity,

712
00:32:16,599 --> 00:32:18,519
it will become very difficult.

713
00:32:19,920 --> 00:32:23,079
I will send someone
to keep an eye on them.

714
00:32:25,120 --> 00:32:26,390
(22nd day of the fourth month, 1911)

715
00:32:26,390 --> 00:32:27,770
(Grain in Ear is 18 days away)

716
00:32:28,768 --> 00:32:30,208
(Dagu, Tianjin)

717
00:32:36,640 --> 00:32:38,359
You really are a scholar.

718
00:32:38,359 --> 00:32:39,240
You just realize that?

719
00:32:44,680 --> 00:32:46,000
When I'm not on official business,

720
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:47,240
I don't wear the constable's uniform.

721
00:32:49,279 --> 00:32:50,799
With your outfit

722
00:32:51,480 --> 00:32:53,240
and the books in this room,

723
00:32:54,599 --> 00:32:55,400
if you don't tell,

724
00:32:56,039 --> 00:32:57,440
who would know you're a constable?

725
00:33:00,359 --> 00:33:02,079
My father has taught me to read
since I was little.

726
00:33:02,599 --> 00:33:03,720
I've become used to it.

727
00:33:04,200 --> 00:33:05,640
When I'm not busy,

728
00:33:05,640 --> 00:33:07,160
I don't even know what to do
if I don't read.

729
00:33:07,160 --> 00:33:08,240
Don't you practice martial arts?

730
00:33:08,480 --> 00:33:10,079
Dagu is a small place.

731
00:33:10,759 --> 00:33:11,839
There aren't many bad people.

732
00:33:12,480 --> 00:33:14,144
Practicing martial arts
is more of a waste.

733
00:33:15,880 --> 00:33:17,359
Sometimes I go to see my master.

734
00:33:17,359 --> 00:33:18,599
I will practice with him.

735
00:33:18,799 --> 00:33:19,559
He will admonish me.

736
00:33:21,480 --> 00:33:22,519
How?

737
00:33:22,640 --> 00:33:24,039
My master has a lisp.

738
00:33:24,680 --> 00:33:25,880
He just hits me.

739
00:33:25,880 --> 00:33:27,359
He will admonish me

740
00:33:27,480 --> 00:33:28,400
if I don't practice hard.

741
00:33:29,799 --> 00:33:30,920
Who is your master?

742
00:33:31,559 --> 00:33:32,640
You're so powerful.

743
00:33:33,160 --> 00:33:35,240
Your master must
be a martial arts expert.

744
00:33:38,519 --> 00:33:39,119
I don't know.

745
00:33:39,839 --> 00:33:41,480
I've asked him several times,
but he won't tell.

746
00:33:47,440 --> 00:33:48,519
But I guess

747
00:33:48,680 --> 00:33:50,640
he was a martial arts expert before.

748
00:33:51,319 --> 00:33:53,599
Unfortunately, he injured his brain

749
00:33:53,599 --> 00:33:54,880
and became deranged.

750
00:33:55,240 --> 00:33:56,319
Now,

751
00:33:57,279 --> 00:33:58,640
he doesn't even remember who he is.

752
00:34:04,359 --> 00:34:06,440
In my second year as a constable,

753
00:34:07,160 --> 00:34:08,199
I caught a few bandits.

754
00:34:08,719 --> 00:34:09,920
I was awarded.

755
00:34:10,079 --> 00:34:11,440
So I built a house for my master.

756
00:34:11,880 --> 00:34:12,519
This one.

757
00:34:14,280 --> 00:34:16,920
I thought if he lived closer to me,

758
00:34:17,239 --> 00:34:18,440
I could take care of him.

759
00:34:18,559 --> 00:34:19,519
Unexpectedly,

760
00:34:20,159 --> 00:34:21,599
he just took a glance inside

761
00:34:21,800 --> 00:34:22,840
and never went in again.

762
00:34:23,639 --> 00:34:24,599
I failed to persuade him.

763
00:34:26,559 --> 00:34:28,480
Fortunately, his kung fu is great.

764
00:34:28,559 --> 00:34:30,239
So running around hasn't been a problem.

765
00:34:31,360 --> 00:34:33,960
That's why I occasionally go to see him

766
00:34:34,440 --> 00:34:35,239
and buy him some food.

767
00:34:39,440 --> 00:34:41,639
Are you going to see him this time?

768
00:34:43,599 --> 00:34:45,760
To be honest,

769
00:34:45,760 --> 00:34:47,079
I don't even know what to do.

770
00:34:47,920 --> 00:34:49,800
The senior I met before
asked me to come back.

771
00:34:50,599 --> 00:34:51,599
I've seen him twice.

772
00:34:52,039 --> 00:34:52,920
He's advised me twice.

773
00:34:53,519 --> 00:34:54,639
There must be a reason for it.

774
00:34:54,639 --> 00:34:55,679
So I came back.

775
00:34:56,519 --> 00:34:57,800
Since I don't know what to do,

776
00:34:58,679 --> 00:34:59,639
I'll go see my master.

777
00:35:05,119 --> 00:35:06,119
How come

778
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:08,920
Ding Yu doesn't come back with you?

779
00:35:11,719 --> 00:35:13,199
Why so many questions today?

780
00:35:15,400 --> 00:35:16,960
The 43rd Association
can't enter the capital.

781
00:35:17,679 --> 00:35:19,079
Yu went to notify them
to arrive tomorrow.

782
00:35:21,519 --> 00:35:22,840
But even if they're here,

783
00:35:23,360 --> 00:35:25,000
I don't know what to do with them.

784
00:35:26,519 --> 00:35:27,880
Then just stop thinking about it.

785
00:35:28,000 --> 00:35:29,920
Give yourself a break.

786
00:35:32,000 --> 00:35:32,920
I'll boil some water.

787
00:35:57,079 --> 00:35:58,480
You usually cook yourself?

788
00:36:01,280 --> 00:36:02,559
In Dagu County Yamen,

789
00:36:02,559 --> 00:36:04,360
our county magistrate loves to cook.

790
00:36:04,639 --> 00:36:06,440
When we're not on official duty,

791
00:36:06,440 --> 00:36:07,840
he cooks in the backyard.

792
00:36:07,840 --> 00:36:09,199
He also studies various recipes.

793
00:36:09,559 --> 00:36:10,920
We just eat with him.

794
00:36:10,920 --> 00:36:12,199
I don't need to cook.

795
00:36:12,440 --> 00:36:13,719
You told me

796
00:36:14,360 --> 00:36:16,000
you are the strongest
in the county yamen.

797
00:36:16,440 --> 00:36:17,360
Of course.

798
00:36:17,360 --> 00:36:18,320
My master taught me.

799
00:36:18,320 --> 00:36:20,639
So what sect is your master from?

800
00:36:20,719 --> 00:36:21,760
How should I know?

801
00:36:22,039 --> 00:36:23,400
You know kung fu.

802
00:36:23,760 --> 00:36:24,840
You can't even tell?

803
00:36:24,840 --> 00:36:25,880
I really can't tell.

804
00:36:26,840 --> 00:36:28,320
Even Muqing can't tell what kind

805
00:36:28,320 --> 00:36:29,280
of kung fu I practice.

806
00:36:29,360 --> 00:36:31,320
So what do you normally practice?

807
00:36:31,920 --> 00:36:32,559
Running.

808
00:36:33,159 --> 00:36:33,880
Running?

809
00:36:35,400 --> 00:36:36,480
(If I run too slowly,)

810
00:36:36,480 --> 00:36:38,039
(my master will hit me with stones.)

811
00:36:41,639 --> 00:36:43,320
I'm running.

812
00:36:59,440 --> 00:36:59,968
Master.

813
00:37:08,280 --> 00:37:09,280
(He's very strict.)

814
00:37:10,480 --> 00:37:12,599
(If I slack off, he'll hit me.)

815
00:37:31,679 --> 00:37:32,400
Hungry?

816
00:37:32,519 --> 00:37:33,400
I'll get you some food.

817
00:37:36,119 --> 00:37:37,360
I'll cook.

818
00:37:37,920 --> 00:37:39,880
Cooking is a woman's job.

819
00:37:42,480 --> 00:37:44,000
Gentlemen stay away from the kitchen.

820
00:37:44,280 --> 00:37:45,599
Aren't you a scholar?

821
00:37:48,840 --> 00:37:49,800
Mencius said

822
00:37:49,920 --> 00:37:51,360
when the gentleman saw the animals,

823
00:37:51,360 --> 00:37:52,679
he couldn't bear to see them die

824
00:37:52,679 --> 00:37:53,880
or eat their meat.

825
00:37:53,880 --> 00:37:55,440
So the gentleman stays away
from the kitchen.

826
00:37:55,679 --> 00:37:56,519
In a word,

827
00:37:57,280 --> 00:37:58,840
no slaughter.

828
00:37:59,800 --> 00:38:00,880
It's not that I mustn't cook.

829
00:38:05,800 --> 00:38:07,559
I found a box of liquor in the kitchen.

830
00:38:08,880 --> 00:38:10,960
Dagu County Yamen
distributed them during the festivals.

831
00:38:11,159 --> 00:38:12,719
I rarely drink when I'm alone.

832
00:38:13,400 --> 00:38:14,559
Today you're not alone.

833
00:38:14,960 --> 00:38:15,840
Let's have a drink.

834
00:38:17,880 --> 00:38:18,464
Okay.

835
00:38:32,280 --> 00:38:32,880
Here's to you.

836
00:38:33,760 --> 00:38:34,320
To me?

837
00:38:34,960 --> 00:38:35,679
Why?

838
00:38:35,880 --> 00:38:37,840
Without you,

